	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Manage Google Tasks without leaving Alfred.

## Setup

1. Create a Google Cloud project and enable the **Tasks API**
2. Create a **Desktop** OAuth client and download `client_secret.json`
3. Run in Terminal:
`mkdir -p ~/Library/Application\ Support/Alfred/Workflow\ Data/com.rhuss.gtasks/`
`cp client_secret.json ~/Library/Application\ Support/Alfred/Workflow\ Data/com.rhuss.gtasks/`
4. Type `gt login` in Alfred to authenticate

Full instructions: [README](https://github.com/rhuss/alfred-google-tasks-workflow)

## Commands

- `gt login` — Authenticate with Google
- `gt add Buy groceries, tomorrow` — Create task with due date
- `gt add Call dentist, friday #Work` — Create task in specific list
- `gt list` — Show tasks grouped by timeframe
- `gt list #Work` — Filter by list
- `gt open` — Open Google Tasks in browser
- `gt logout` — Disconnect account

## Dates

Supported: **today**, **tomorrow**, **monday**–**sunday**, **next week**, **2026-07-15**, **07-15**

German: **heute**, **morgen**, **uebermorgen**, **montag**–**sonntag**, **naechste woche**

## Lists

Add `#ListName` at the end to target a list. Lists are auto-created if new. Hyphens and underscores become spaces: `#My-List` = "My List".</string>
